    "description": "KYCOM Holdings Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, consults, plans, designs, develops, and maintains information systems in Japan. The company operates in four segments: Information Processing Business, Real Estate Business, Rental Business, and Wireless Solutions Business. It offers system development, IT consulting and services, infrastructure construction, operation and maintenance support, data entry work, help desk, outsourcing contracted business, development and sale of fingerprint authentication systems, and leasing of office equipment and computer devices. The company also provides wireless communication solutions, including installation, repair, inspection, and maintenance of wireless equipment, as well as disaster prevention. In addition, it is involved in the management of apartment buildings; solar power generation; and car rental business. The company was formerly known as Kyodo Computer Holdings Co., Ltd. and changed its name to KYCOM Holdings Co., Ltd. in June 2011. KYCOM Holdings Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1968 and is headquartered in Fukui, Japan."
